featured_reviews.review_id:
The calm mosque of Bhiwandi.
Mosques are always peaceful but this is the most peaceful I have ever seen.
Preachings here are very good mostly related to the subjects of morals and humanity.
Unlike other mosques of the area they don't use loud speakers for Namaz (prayer).Azan (call to prayer) and Bayan (preaching) is also done in such a way that the sound is not much and one can feel peace inside his heart by hearing it.
One of the best mosques I have ever visited or perhaps one of the best in the world.
Though it is in poor or middle class locality and construction is not so nice but one can really feel close to God here.
